sample_extract_protocol_ch1: CD4SP thymocytes were sorted and fixed in 1% formaldehyde. Cells were sonicated, lysates clarified, and protein-DNA complexes immunoprecipitated., Libraries were prepared and sequenced following standard Illumina protocols
sample_data_processing: Alignment--bowtie2 (v2.3.4) --end-to-end --sensitive --no-unal, Filtering with samtools (v1.6) -q 20, Sorting and indexing with samtools, Convert to bed with bedtools (v2.29.2), Remove blacklisted regions with bedtools, Convert bamfile to counts per million normalized bigwig with Deeptools (v3.3.0), Peak calling with Macs2 (v2.2.4) --nomodel --nolambda --extsize 300 -q 0.9 --keep-dup-all
supplementary_files_format_and_content: Counts per million normalized bigwig file

sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Nuclei were isolated following the recommended protocol from 10X Genomics. Transposition and scATACseq capture was performed with the 10X Chromium Single Cell ATAC Solution (v1.0) , following the manufacturer's recommended protocol, Libraries were run on a NextSeq500, Parameters:50bp (Read1), 8bp (Index1), 16bp (Index2), 50bp (Read2), Indexing 2 samples (SCAF1016_II, SI-NA-G5; SCAF1017_B, SI-NA-G6)
sample_data_processing: Basecalls performed with Illumina RTA 2.4.6, Demultiplexing with Bcl2fastq 2.17, 10x data for scATAC samples are run through cellranger ATAC (v1.0) software to produce the fastqfiles, The fastq files are processed through cellranger, including alignment, identification of cut sites, and peak calling.
